column5: Went out for some fishin' for some panfish... didn't really matter what we caught, just hoping to catch something. After an hour we found the fish, bluegills n crappie. They were all in an area about the size of my driveway... if you casted even 10 feet out of that spot, nothing... Overall we caught probably 50 crappies (all good sized) and numerous bluegills. I kept 8 for dinner tonight. This fish at the top I think was the biggest.
Always happy to see bigger crappie reports! Cheers!
Those be some nice slabs. Makes me hungee
Nice catch!!!,at least you were able to locate them in such a small area.  .
Sweet nuggets of crappie love!!!  Enjoy the buffet.
Wow!  I spent 4 hrs looking for them at the north east end of Pigeon and the Balds.  Natta.  2-5ft. shorelines, points, quiet bays.  water temp 53
Nice feed there, I hope too get into some Dalrymple crappie on Thursday they are usually thick in the canal this time of year.
Nice haul for a day on the water !!!! What time is dinner ???
